questions.question:
Consider the following recursive function execution flow:

```
void foo(int x) {
    if (x <= 0) return;
    print(x);
    foo(x - 1);
    print(x);
}
```
What is the exact output sequence for foo(3)?

The Ackermann function is defined recursively as:
A(m, n) = n + 1 if m = 0;
A(m, n) = A(m-1, 1) if m > 0, n = 0;
A(m, n) = A(m-1, A(m, n-1)) if m > 0, n > 0.
Compute the exact value of A(1, 2).

Consider this custom tri-recursive function:
```python
def f(n):
    if n <= 0:
        return 1
    if n == 1:
        return 2
    return f(n-1) + f(n-2) + f(n-3)
```
What is the output value of f(3)?
